text.section:
A person is not required to hold a certificate under KRS 311.864 to 311.890 if the person is:
A student enrolled in a surgical assistant education program approved by the board who is assisting in a surgical operation that is an integral part of the program of study;
A surgical assistant employed in the service of the federal government while performing surgical assisting duties related to that employment;
A health care worker, licensed or certified within this Commonwealth, acting within the scope of the person's license;
A registered nurse or licensed practical nurse;
A certified physician assistant; or
An individual employed by a hospital who is performing the duties of a surgical assistant under the direct supervision of a registered nurse.
